WEBVTT

1
00:00:00.210 --> 00:00:02.210
(THEME MUSIC PLAYING)

2
00:00:58.000 --> 00:01:00.120
(NARRATOR READING)

3
00:01:00.121 --> 00:01:02.250
NARRATOR:
"Journey of Memories."

4
00:01:08.080 --> 00:01:09.750
MAKINI:
Look! The Tree of Life!

5
00:01:10.170 --> 00:01:12.580
This is the next
<i> moja kwa moja</i> stone,
all right.

6
00:01:12.581 --> 00:01:15.170
Then we're still
on the right path
to the Tree of Life.

7
00:01:15.171 --> 00:01:17.540
But that painting
shows a river.

8
00:01:17.541 --> 00:01:20.000
You call this a river?

9
00:01:20.001 --> 00:01:22.420
It might have been
a big river at some point.

10
00:01:22.790 --> 00:01:26.000
Landscapes can
change over time
or with the seasons.

11
00:01:26.001 --> 00:01:27.790
Just like the dry season
back home.

12
00:01:28.120 --> 00:01:29.830
Ono, what's the
next landmark?

13
00:01:30.250 --> 00:01:31.580
<i> Nawaza...</i>

14
00:01:34.580 --> 00:01:37.460
<i> It's a pool of water.
 With rocks all around it.</i>

15
00:01:37.670 --> 00:01:39.210
Anga?
Yep.

16
00:01:40.250 --> 00:01:43.250
Oh! I remember
this river now.

17
00:01:43.251 --> 00:01:45.620
I was here
with my mom and dad
when I was little.

18
00:01:45.621 --> 00:01:47.540
On my first trip
to the Tree of Life.

19
00:01:49.330 --> 00:01:51.120
It had a lot more water
back then.

20
00:01:51.121 --> 00:01:54.460
Well, any river
I can hop across
has enough water for me.

21
00:01:54.461 --> 00:01:57.120
So, Makini,
was Rafiki here with you too?

22
00:01:57.121 --> 00:01:58.580
Nope.

23
00:01:58.581 --> 00:02:01.290
My mom and dad were
taking me to the Tree of Life
to meet Rafiki.

24
00:02:01.291 --> 00:02:02.830
We had so much fun!

25
00:02:06.210 --> 00:02:08.620
Ooh! Cold! Cold! Cold!

26
00:02:10.000 --> 00:02:11.290
(GRUNTS)

27
00:02:11.291 --> 00:02:14.120
(SHIVERING)
You're right, Makini!
This water's freezing!

28
00:02:14.121 --> 00:02:15.580
(LAUGHS) Dad!

29
00:02:16.040 --> 00:02:18.540
Oh, Kitendo, my love.
(CHUCKLES)

30
00:02:18.541 --> 00:02:19.790
You know the saying.

31
00:02:19.791 --> 00:02:22.080
"Test the water
before diving in."

32
00:02:22.081 --> 00:02:24.170
(CHUCKLES)
But then again...

33
00:02:24.420 --> 00:02:26.170
(GASPING)

34
00:02:26.171 --> 00:02:27.830
"If you want
to take a bath,

35
00:02:28.170 --> 00:02:31.040
"you should not be afraid
to get cold."

36
00:02:31.041 --> 00:02:33.290
As usual,
you are right, Fikiri.

37
00:02:33.830 --> 00:02:37.080
But my way is way more fun!

38
00:02:38.040 --> 00:02:39.580
(ALL LAUGH)

39
00:02:42.790 --> 00:02:43.880
FULI: Makini!

40
00:02:44.120 --> 00:02:46.000
Oops. Sorry, Fuli.

41
00:02:46.001 --> 00:02:48.080
BUNGA: <i> Zuka Zama!</i>

42
00:02:48.790 --> 00:02:50.830
Careful, Bunga!
You know the saying,

43
00:02:50.831 --> 00:02:52.920
"Test the water
before diving in!"

44
00:02:52.921 --> 00:02:54.960
(SCOFFS)
Where's the fun in that?

45
00:02:54.961 --> 00:02:57.170
(CHUCKLES)
You sound like my dad.

46
00:02:58.540 --> 00:03:01.670
Hey, Anga!
You find the next
<i>moja kwa moja</i> stone?

47
00:03:01.671 --> 00:03:04.290
I found a rocky pool
with small boulders.

48
00:03:04.291 --> 00:03:05.500
But it's dry.

49
00:03:05.501 --> 00:03:07.670
Oh. That doesn't
seem right.

50
00:03:07.671 --> 00:03:10.040
The pool I remember
had lots of water.

51
00:03:10.041 --> 00:03:11.750
And the boulders
were huge!

52
00:03:11.751 --> 00:03:14.380
It matches
Ono's description.
It's just...

53
00:03:14.710 --> 00:03:15.960
Drier.

54
00:03:15.961 --> 00:03:17.880
Well, if this river
has less water,

55
00:03:17.881 --> 00:03:20.330
it makes sense
that the pool
would be dry, too.

56
00:03:20.331 --> 00:03:23.040
Wait! I remember
those trees!

57
00:03:23.041 --> 00:03:25.540
There's a waterfall
down there! It's amazing!

58
00:03:25.790 --> 00:03:28.620
Uh, that's the opposite
direction of the pool.

59
00:03:28.621 --> 00:03:30.790
But it's so beautiful!

60
00:03:30.791 --> 00:03:33.040
Can we go, Kion?
Please?

61
00:03:33.380 --> 00:03:37.210
Well, I guess a little detour
out of our way would be okay.

62
00:03:37.540 --> 00:03:38.670
Lead on, Makini!

63
00:03:38.671 --> 00:03:40.040
(WHOOPING)

64
00:03:43.540 --> 00:03:45.170
MAKINI: Uh, right
around this corner.

65
00:03:46.040 --> 00:03:48.500
(GASPS) We're here!
This is it!

66
00:03:48.880 --> 00:03:50.170
Or was it?

67
00:03:50.420 --> 00:03:52.040
Uh, am I just
not seeing it?

68
00:03:52.290 --> 00:03:53.920
Well, it used to be here.

69
00:03:53.921 --> 00:03:56.290
Water was pouring
down this rock.

70
00:03:57.380 --> 00:03:58.960
(GASPS) Oh, look! See?

71
00:03:59.170 --> 00:04:01.620
I wouldn't
call that pouring.

72
00:04:02.580 --> 00:04:04.460
Look!
One of Rafiki's paintings.

73
00:04:04.920 --> 00:04:06.670
That wasn't here last time.

74
00:04:06.671 --> 00:04:09.080
I wonder if it's
<i> a moja kwa moja</i> stone.

75
00:04:11.080 --> 00:04:12.750
Nope. No Tree of Life.

76
00:04:12.960 --> 00:04:15.040
But now we know
this used to be a waterfall.

77
00:04:15.540 --> 00:04:17.920
Maybe Rafiki
saw the waterfall

78
00:04:17.921 --> 00:04:19.920
on his trip
to the Tree of Life

79
00:04:19.921 --> 00:04:21.920
and painted it
just because it was <i> poa.</i>

80
00:04:21.921 --> 00:04:23.080
That makes sense.

81
00:04:23.081 --> 00:04:25.000
He paints things
all the time
in the Pride Lands.

82
00:04:25.540 --> 00:04:28.250
So, the next
<i> moja kwa moja</i> stone
is this way.

83
00:04:28.620 --> 00:04:30.040
KION: Let's go, everyone.

84
00:04:31.420 --> 00:04:33.960
Did you see the waterfall
with your mom and dad too?

85
00:04:33.961 --> 00:04:37.920
Yeah! I saw so many
amazing things on our trip
to the Tree of Life!

86
00:04:38.330 --> 00:04:42.420
Oh! I remember
something really fun
down that way! Come on!

87
00:04:42.421 --> 00:04:44.250
Makini?
Where are you going now?

88
00:04:44.620 --> 00:04:46.000
See this rock?

89
00:04:46.001 --> 00:04:48.620
It has a big hole
near the bottom that you can
stick your arm through!

90
00:04:48.621 --> 00:04:50.120
I wanna try! I wanna try!

91
00:04:50.121 --> 00:04:51.330
So, where's the hole?

92
00:04:51.331 --> 00:04:52.540
Think I can get
my head in it?

93
00:04:53.540 --> 00:04:54.920
I don't see it.

94
00:04:55.790 --> 00:04:57.500
I was sure
this was the rock.

95
00:04:57.501 --> 00:04:59.170
But maybe it's not.

96
00:04:59.460 --> 00:05:01.960
Sorry, Makini,
but we have to keep moving.

97
00:05:06.460 --> 00:05:08.960
(GROANS)
Lousy rock with no hole!

98
00:05:09.380 --> 00:05:10.460
Ow!

99
00:05:14.500 --> 00:05:17.080
Okay. So maybe
that wasn't the right rock.

100
00:05:17.500 --> 00:05:19.250
(GASPS)
But there is something

101
00:05:19.251 --> 00:05:20.960
really amazing
right over there!

102
00:05:21.460 --> 00:05:22.460
Seriously?

103
00:05:24.210 --> 00:05:26.210
So, what are we
looking at?

104
00:05:26.211 --> 00:05:27.790
That mountain right there!

105
00:05:27.791 --> 00:05:29.790
The one that looks
like a monkey's face!

106
00:05:30.830 --> 00:05:31.960
Don't see it.

107
00:05:32.290 --> 00:05:35.380
Hmm... We might
have to get lower.

108
00:05:37.210 --> 00:05:39.380
And tilt
our heads a little.

109
00:05:40.920 --> 00:05:43.080
It doesn't look
like anything at all.

110
00:05:43.081 --> 00:05:44.830
Can we go now?
Good idea.

111
00:05:46.330 --> 00:05:47.710
Sorry, Makini.

112
00:05:47.711 --> 00:05:50.040
Maybe you're remembering
a different mountain.

113
00:05:59.880 --> 00:06:01.040
Here we are.

114
00:06:01.250 --> 00:06:02.380
Finally.

115
00:06:02.381 --> 00:06:04.170
Yes! This is it!

116
00:06:04.171 --> 00:06:06.210
And it looks just
the way I remember it.

117
00:06:07.420 --> 00:06:08.880
Except there's no water.

118
00:06:09.120 --> 00:06:10.710
And I thought
the boulders were bigger.

119
00:06:10.880 --> 00:06:12.250
Maybe you were smaller?

120
00:06:12.251 --> 00:06:13.420
Oh, yeah.

121
00:06:13.421 --> 00:06:16.040
This painting matches
what I saw on Rafiki's map.

122
00:06:16.041 --> 00:06:17.040
Makini?

123
00:06:21.330 --> 00:06:23.750
Yep. That's
a <i> moja kwa moja</i> stone.

124
00:06:23.751 --> 00:06:25.120
Ono, what's next?

125
00:06:25.710 --> 00:06:26.880
<i> Nawaza.</i>

126
00:06:28.290 --> 00:06:32.250
<i> The next landmark
 is four white flowers
 in the shape of a diamond.</i>

127
00:06:32.251 --> 00:06:34.540
They're in a field
of smaller white flowers.

128
00:06:34.880 --> 00:06:36.620
Anga?
Yep.

129
00:06:36.621 --> 00:06:37.920
<i> Anga lenga!</i>

130
00:06:39.250 --> 00:06:41.210
I don't remember
any white flowers,

131
00:06:41.211 --> 00:06:42.920
but I do remember
a really amazing...

132
00:06:42.921 --> 00:06:44.000
ALL: No!

133
00:06:45.290 --> 00:06:48.080
Sorry, Makini.
But no more detours.

134
00:06:48.081 --> 00:06:49.500
We need to keep moving.

135
00:06:49.880 --> 00:06:50.880
(SIGHS)

136
00:06:53.080 --> 00:06:54.540
Don't be sad, Makini.

137
00:06:54.541 --> 00:06:56.250
Your detours
are really fun.

138
00:06:56.251 --> 00:06:57.620
Thanks, Beshte.

139
00:06:57.621 --> 00:07:00.580
I had a lot of fun
with my mom and dad
the last time I was here.

140
00:07:00.581 --> 00:07:04.830
In fact, this is where
they first told me
I might be a Royal Mjuzi.

141
00:07:04.831 --> 00:07:07.420
Really? <i> Poa.</i>

142
00:07:07.421 --> 00:07:09.830
Yeah. It was <i> poa.</i>

143
00:07:12.460 --> 00:07:13.920
FIKIRI:
Time to go, Makini!

144
00:07:13.921 --> 00:07:16.580
(MAKINI LAUGHS)
KITENDO:
Makini, wrong way!

145
00:07:17.080 --> 00:07:18.960
Rafiki should make paintings

146
00:07:18.961 --> 00:07:21.040
that mark the way
to the Tree of Life.

147
00:07:21.250 --> 00:07:22.830
(LAUGHING)

148
00:07:23.210 --> 00:07:24.330
Whoa!

149
00:07:24.331 --> 00:07:26.790
Whoa, whoa, whoa!

150
00:07:27.120 --> 00:07:28.540
(SIGHS)

151
00:07:28.541 --> 00:07:30.620
Well, that way does
look more fun, doesn't it?

152
00:07:30.621 --> 00:07:32.120
(LAUGHS) Yeah!

153
00:07:32.121 --> 00:07:35.460
But this is the way
we must go to get
to the Tree of Life.

154
00:07:35.461 --> 00:07:36.670
Why?

155
00:07:36.671 --> 00:07:39.040
Because Rafiki
would like to meet you.

156
00:07:39.041 --> 00:07:42.670
Why?
Rafiki is a Royal Mjuzi.

157
00:07:42.671 --> 00:07:46.290
And he believes
that you may also grow up
to be a Royal Mjuzi.

158
00:07:46.620 --> 00:07:49.380
But only the
Voices of the Past
at the Tree of Life

159
00:07:49.381 --> 00:07:50.710
will let him know
for sure.

160
00:07:50.711 --> 00:07:52.330
Oh!

161
00:07:52.540 --> 00:07:54.250
But... But why me?

162
00:07:54.580 --> 00:07:57.040
Because you're wise
like your mother.

163
00:07:57.041 --> 00:08:00.330
Or because you're curious
and fun like your father.

164
00:08:00.670 --> 00:08:03.540
But mainly,
because you are you.

165
00:08:03.541 --> 00:08:04.670
(GIGGLES)

166
00:08:04.671 --> 00:08:07.880
But no matter what,
you'll always be
our Makini.

167
00:08:07.881 --> 00:08:09.960
And we'll always
be with you.

168
00:08:09.961 --> 00:08:11.710
Until you're ready
to go out on your own.

169
00:08:13.830 --> 00:08:15.960
KION: Anga! You find
the white flowers?

170
00:08:15.961 --> 00:08:17.120
Nope.

171
00:08:17.121 --> 00:08:18.830
Great! Then let's...

172
00:08:18.831 --> 00:08:20.170
Wait, what?

173
00:08:20.171 --> 00:08:21.830
No sign of white flowers.

174
00:08:21.831 --> 00:08:23.670
Or anywhere
flowers would grow.

175
00:08:23.920 --> 00:08:25.460
So, what did you see?

176
00:08:25.461 --> 00:08:27.210
Desert straight ahead.

177
00:08:27.211 --> 00:08:29.170
Oh! I remember the desert!

178
00:08:29.171 --> 00:08:31.790
We have to cross it.
And head toward the cliffs.

179
00:08:31.791 --> 00:08:33.210
I didn't see any cliffs.

180
00:08:33.211 --> 00:08:35.830
There aren't any cliffs
in Rafiki's painting either.

181
00:08:35.831 --> 00:08:37.420
Just the field of flowers.

182
00:08:37.421 --> 00:08:40.290
But the river, waterfall
and pool are all dried up.

183
00:08:40.291 --> 00:08:43.120
Maybe there used
to be flowers here
when there was water.

184
00:08:43.540 --> 00:08:45.040
I don't remember flowers.

185
00:08:45.041 --> 00:08:47.380
But I definitely
remember the desert.

186
00:08:47.381 --> 00:08:50.750
We walked
all the way across it
until we reached the cliffs.

187
00:08:50.960 --> 00:08:55.710
Kion, Makini's memories
haven't exactly
been reliable so far.

188
00:08:55.711 --> 00:08:59.380
I know. But if we
can't find the next
<i> moja kwa moja</i> stone,

189
00:08:59.381 --> 00:09:01.170
we can't find
the Tree of Life.

190
00:09:01.171 --> 00:09:04.960
Makini is the only
one of us who's been
to the Tree of Life before.

191
00:09:04.961 --> 00:09:06.750
Isn't that why Rafiki
sent her with us?

192
00:09:09.330 --> 00:09:11.420
Okay, Makini.
Lead the way!

193
00:09:11.620 --> 00:09:12.620
Yes!

194
00:09:13.210 --> 00:09:15.460
Okay, everybody,
follow me!

195
00:09:28.330 --> 00:09:30.420
(SIGHS IN EXASPERATION)

196
00:09:30.880 --> 00:09:33.000
Beshte, are you okay?

197
00:09:33.290 --> 00:09:35.250
Yeah, I guess.

198
00:09:35.251 --> 00:09:39.040
<i>Hapana!</i> Beshte!
You're starting
to get sunburned!

199
00:09:39.041 --> 00:09:41.170
What? Everyone, stop!

200
00:09:41.580 --> 00:09:43.670
We've gotta find
Beshte some shade!

201
00:09:43.671 --> 00:09:46.420
Kion's right. Hippos
don't do well in the sun!

202
00:09:46.750 --> 00:09:48.420
There's no shade anywhere.

203
00:09:48.960 --> 00:09:50.540
Nothing but sand.

204
00:09:52.120 --> 00:09:54.210
Ooh! That's better.

205
00:09:54.211 --> 00:09:56.420
Hey, that's a great idea!

206
00:09:56.670 --> 00:10:00.460
Anga! Can you keep
flying above Beshte
so he's in your shadow?

207
00:10:00.461 --> 00:10:01.580
I guess.

208
00:10:01.581 --> 00:10:03.750
Thanks, Anga.
No problem.

209
00:10:14.040 --> 00:10:16.880
Makini, you're sure
we're going the right way?

210
00:10:16.881 --> 00:10:18.080
I'm sure!

211
00:10:18.081 --> 00:10:20.120
Straight across the desert
toward the cliffs!

212
00:10:20.380 --> 00:10:22.960
Guys, I know it's cooler
in the shade,

213
00:10:22.961 --> 00:10:25.960
but Beshte might feel better
if you weren't
riding on his back.

214
00:10:27.040 --> 00:10:28.580
ANGA:
Everyone, look out!

215
00:10:30.880 --> 00:10:33.210
(WIND BLOWING)

216
00:10:40.080 --> 00:10:41.710
(SPITS AND GROANS)

217
00:10:42.120 --> 00:10:44.210
(EXHALES) Thanks, Anga.

218
00:10:44.211 --> 00:10:45.330
Indeed.

219
00:10:45.331 --> 00:10:46.880
And thanks for the lift,
Beshte.

220
00:10:46.881 --> 00:10:48.540
Yeah. Thanks, Beshte.

221
00:10:48.541 --> 00:10:49.880
(LOUD THUMP)

222
00:10:49.881 --> 00:10:51.250
Uh, what was that?

223
00:10:52.040 --> 00:10:54.120
(LOUD THUMP)
There it is again.

224
00:10:54.121 --> 00:10:56.960
Whoa! Let me try.
(THUMPING)

225
00:10:57.170 --> 00:11:02.080
(LAUGHS) Whatever it is,
it's un-Bunga-lievable!

226
00:11:02.081 --> 00:11:03.330
ONO: Hmm.

227
00:11:03.500 --> 00:11:05.540
This must be
a booming sand dune.

228
00:11:05.541 --> 00:11:08.540
I've heard about them,
but never actually heard them.

229
00:11:08.541 --> 00:11:10.790
Well, wait 'til
you hear this!

230
00:11:11.500 --> 00:11:14.210
(LOUD THUMPING CONTINUES)

231
00:11:14.211 --> 00:11:16.420
Oh! I remember this, too.

232
00:11:16.421 --> 00:11:19.120
(THUMPING CONTINUES)
My mom and dad and I
had so much fun here!

233
00:11:19.121 --> 00:11:20.250
(GROANS)

234
00:11:21.080 --> 00:11:22.080
Makini.

235
00:11:23.250 --> 00:11:25.250
Is this why
you brought us out here?

236
00:11:25.251 --> 00:11:27.120
Because you thought
it would be fun?

237
00:11:27.121 --> 00:11:28.880
What? No, Kion...

238
00:11:28.881 --> 00:11:31.420
We don't have time
for any more
of your detours!

239
00:11:31.710 --> 00:11:34.420
Kion, Makini never said
this was a detour.

240
00:11:35.040 --> 00:11:36.250
(GROANS)

241
00:11:36.251 --> 00:11:37.380
You sure you're okay?

242
00:11:37.381 --> 00:11:39.210
Maybe you should have
some Tuliza.

243
00:11:39.211 --> 00:11:41.540
(GROANS) I don't need Tuliza!

244
00:11:41.541 --> 00:11:42.790
Kion...

245
00:11:44.420 --> 00:11:46.250
I... I'm sorry.

246
00:11:46.880 --> 00:11:50.040
I'm hot, tired, thirsty,
and covered with sand.

247
00:11:50.380 --> 00:11:52.620
But that's no excuse.

248
00:11:52.621 --> 00:11:54.120
I shouldn't have yelled.

249
00:11:54.121 --> 00:11:56.500
So... If we're
all good again,

